	<section id="recipe">
		<p>
			After my first trip to Egypt back in 2010, when I was
			still a vegetarian, I discovered real tahini (or as
			they call it there, <q>tahina</q>, and ate it with
			everything.  
			As salad dressing, as meze, as sandwich
			spread... I could not get enough of it. It was like
			peanut butter, only different - more exotic, more
			versatile, and better. 
		
	     </p>
		<table class="ingredients">
			<caption>Ingredients</caption>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th class="amount" colspan="2">amount</th>
					<th class="name">name</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"><span data-lilachop-amount="1"></span>&#8211;<span data-lilachop-amount="2"></span></td>
				<td class="unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="name">tahini</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="1"></td>
				<td class="unit">scoop</td>
				<td class="name">raw vegan protein powder (I used Sunwarrior vanilla)</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="1"></td>
				<td class="unit">cup</td>
				<td class="name">raw almond milk</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="0.5"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td class="name">frozen banana</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"><span data-lilachop-amount="1"></span>&#8211;<span data-lilachop-amount="2"></span></td>
				<td class="unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="name">chia seeds</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="1"></td>
				<td class="unit">tbsp</td>
				<td class="name">organic ground cinnamon</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="1"></td>
				<td class="unit">tsp</td>
				<td class="name">organic ground cardamon</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"><span data-lilachop-amount="1"></span>&#8211;<span data-lilachop-amount="2"></span></td>
				<td class="unit">drops</td>
				<td class="name">liquid vanilla stevia <i>(for sweetness)</i></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount" data-lilachop-amount="1"></td>
				<td class="unit">cup</td>
				<td class="name">ice</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<div class="servings">
			Change servings: 
			<input id="servings" type="number" min="0" step="1" value="1" onchange="changeservings(this.value);" />
		</div>
		<p>
			A few years later I discovered a recipe for a tahini
			protein Smoothie by <u>Nutritionstripped</u>, one of my
			favourite food bloggers and sources of healthy recipes. 
			
			I was overjoyed to replicate my Egypt experience at
			home, and adapted the recipe by adding one of my
			favourite spices: cardamon. It turned out simply
			divine.... a mix of chai and tahini in a nutrition
			bomb.   
		</p>
		<table id="steps">
			<caption>Steps</caption>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th class="amount" colspan="2">time</th>
					<th>instruction</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td>Combine all the ingredients in a blender
					until you get a smooth, creamy
					consistency.</td> 
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td>Pour into a glass and garnish with extra chia seeds.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td>
					Serve cold, and enjoy!
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<p>
			"Cinnamon, spice, and everything nice!" This is one
			hell of a raw vegan treat, packed with nutrients,
			antioxidants, and of course, protein.  Rich and
			unusually nutty-flavoured thanks to the tahini and
			chia, this smoothie packs in the protein and essential
			fats. 
		</p>

		<p>
			<b>Macro-tip:</b>To make it lighter, simply skip the banana. 
		</p>
